That being said, I firmly believe that free market capitalism is the path out of poverty for the poor in the third world. I target women owned businesses because women's rights often don't exist in primitive cultures (they are viewed as property and abused beyond belief) and economic power IS power in these places. IF you read this I need help...

Well I really need a loan to get back on my feet my job went out of business and for the last six months I've been trying find a job with no luck. I have been penny pinching and fall short on my bills... close to being homeless soon. I have been in business for myself, but when my job closed I wasn't financially stable to pay the business bills much less my own and I started borrowing from the business to support myself.
I'm not sure how this site works, but I don't know where else to turn to get help before I lose everything! I speak to GOD everyday guide me through this point in my life of uncertainty. I'm hoping someone with a kind heart can help me get my life back on point. I have a business plan, but I am not credit worthy to apply for a loan through the bank by myself. Ii don't know what to do.
